                "id": "CVE-2015-7970", 
                "modified": "2015-11-02T12:05:06.860-05:00", 
                "summary": "The p2m_pod_emergency_sweep function in arch/x86/mm/p2m-pod.c in Xen 3.4.x, 3.5.x, and 3.6.x is not preemptible, which allows local x86 HVM guest administrators to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption and possibly reboot) via crafted memory contents that triggers a \"time-consuming linear scan,\" related to Populate-on-Demand."
